Docs.summary: Default oversampling factor. Oversampling retrieves a greater set of potential documents to offset the resolution loss due to quantization. This increases the set of results that will be rescored on full-precision vectors. Minimum value is 1, meaning no oversampling (1x). This parameter can only be set when 'enableRescoring' is true. Higher values improve recall at the expense of latency.
